cent of votes in the first round of polling on December 26, said that most
cases of alleged fraud sent to the Constitutional Council were 'completely
without foundation'.
'Other extremist parties which have been rejected by the people are trying
to manipulate the media in order to frighten off these people from the
choice of an Islamic state,' he said.
Observers say that complaints of cheating will make little difference to the
commanding lead seized by the fundamentalists in the first round of voting.
