</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
   By AP-DJ
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
DAEWOO Corp's construction division has received a contract for a Dollars
957m (Pounds 525.8m) highway project in Pakistan, the company says, AP-DJ
reports from Seoul.
The contract, awarded by Pakistan's National Highway Authority, is for a
204-mile road linking Islamabad and Lahore.
The project includes building 74 bridges. Daewoo will handle design, detail
engineering, procurement and construction, with the design fee totalling
Dollars 9m.
Daewoo says the contract is the biggest international road contract awarded
by Pakistan. Construction is scheduled to be completed by April 1995.
South Korea won Pounds 1.7bn worth of foreign construction orders last year,
up 42 per cent from the previous 12 months, AP-DJ reports from Seoul.
The Overseas Construction Association of Korea, a private group of
contractors, said contracts in south-east Asia topped the list, followed by
the Middle East, North America and Africa. Projects under negotiation this
year included a Dollars 1.8bn power plant in Libya.
