<HEADLINE>
FT  07 JAN 92 / Bank sells Pounds 1.3bn of gilts
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
   By PETER NORMAN
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
THE Bank of England sold Pounds 1.32bn of government gilt-edged securities
in November, according to official figures released yesterday, Peter Norman
writes. This prompted City analysts to suggest that the government is close
to funding the public sector borrowing requirement for 1991-92.
The Bank's final monetary statistics for November showed large purchases of
Pounds 1.1bn of gilts by the non-bank private sector during the month,
pointing to strong investor interest among institutions.
According to Mr Don Smith, a UK economist for Greenwell Montagu Gilt-Edged,
the government may have to sell only another Pounds 500m of gilts to fully
fund the Pounds 10.5bn PSBR for 1991-92 forecast in the Treasury's Autumn
Statement.
The Bank revised down slightly its estimate of bank and building society
lending in November - to Pounds 5.5bn from Pounds 5.7bn in provisional
figures published last month.
</TEXT>
