<TEXT>
JAPAN will probably have to set import targets for US cars and car parts to
satisfy American demands, Mr Kozo Watanabe, Japan's international trade and
industry minister, said yesterday, ahead of President Bush's four-day visit,
Reuter reports from Tokyo.
