of foreign-made cars, but some said there were limits to what they could do.
Toyota and Nissan said yesterday they might boost imports further. Sales of
US-made vehicles in Japan for January-November 1991 totalled 27,754, out of
180,852 imported vehicles sold there in the same 11 months.
