<TEXT>
The WARD GROUP has been awarded contracts worth around Pounds 11.6m.
Heading the list is a Pounds 5.8m order from Olympia &amp; York for 7,900 tonnes
of steel and floor decking at B3, B4 and B5 at Canary Wharf.
At the Metro Centre, Gateshead, the company is providing a complete building
package, worth Pounds 1.3m, including steel work, roof and wall cladding,
curtain walling, floor decking, roof ventilators, signage and doors for an
IKEA retail furnishing store.
In Coventry a Pounds 1.7m contract comprises structural steelwork for a
fully automated warehouse and office for Toys 'R' Us, while provision of
steelwork, roof and wall cladding worth Pounds 1.8m is being undertaken for
an office, warehouse and distribution centre owned by Addidas in Stockport.
Other projects include structural steelwork worth Pounds 800,000 for the
Seasalter Viaduct, Kent, and structural steelwork worth Pounds 200,000 for
the Prebend Street Bridge, Bedfordshire.
