<HEADLINE>
FT  06 JAN 92 / International Company News: Merchant bank wins bid battle
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
   By PATRICK BLUM
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
FINANTIA-Sociedade de Investimentos, the Portuguese merchant banking and
investment company, has finally won control of Sofinloc-Sociedade Financeira
de Locacao, the country's leading leasing company, writes Patrick Blum.
After months of bids and counter bids by Finantia and Banco Comercial de
Macau (BCM), the Macao-based bank controlled by Banco Portugues do Atlantico
(BPA), Finantia secured 76.28 per cent of Sofinloc, paying about Esc10.5bn
(Dollars 78m) for over 1.5m shares, at Esc6,933 per share.
</TEXT>
