FT  06 JAN 92 / UK Company News: In brief
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
BhS, a subsidiary of Storehouse which also owns Mothercare, is to sell its
O'Connell Street, Dublin store to Primark, which is part of JC Penney.
Primark, trading as Penneys, has undertaken to employ all existing full time
and part time non-restaurant staff in O'Connell Street.
*****
BARR &amp; WALLACE Arnold Trust has sold its VAG motor dealership in York to
Layerthorpe for Pounds 721,000.
*****
NORTH SEA ASSETS has sold its 48 per cent shareholding in Dramgate for
Pounds 1.2m. The shares will be purchased and redeemed by Dramgate. The book
value of NSA's investment was Pounds 96,000 andproceeds will be applied
towards the reduction of group debt.
